on your own,

01:15:28.339 --> 01:15:30.259
and then you can run Posit Workbench

01:15:30.899 --> 01:15:31.859
which is an idea of like,

01:15:31.859 --> 01:15:34.020
rather than using personal access token,

01:15:34.020 --> 01:15:36.100
it knows who you are and, you know,

01:15:36.100 --> 01:15:37.220
understands the data governance

01:15:37.220 --> 01:15:38.979
and applies that to your user space.

01:15:38.979 --> 01:15:40.899
So you don't have to worry about any credentialing there.

01:15:42.419 --> 01:15:44.819
Okay, we've got about two minutes left.

01:15:44.819 --> 01:15:47.540
So I'm going to ask a possibly trolling question,

01:15:47.540 --> 01:15:50.100
but why not simply call it Python Studio?

01:15:51.939 --> 01:15:53.859
Well, I mean, the real answer there

01:15:53.859 --> 01:15:57.299
is that this is our vision for this,

01:15:57.299 --> 01:15:59.859
is that it is for multiple languages,

01:16:00.660 --> 01:16:01.700
for data science.

01:16:01.700 --> 01:16:03.779
Like today, you know,

01:16:03.779 --> 01:16:05.939
many of us are using R and Python,

01:16:05.939 --> 01:16:08.740
but it is, that may not be true moving forward.

01:16:08.740 --> 01:16:10.660
There's really exciting stuff happening

01:16:10.660 --> 01:16:12.339
in the data science space,

01:16:12.339 --> 01:16:14.419
and we want to build something

01:16:14.419 --> 01:16:18.259
that allows us to have the flexibility

01:16:18.259 --> 01:16:19.779
to add new language packs

01:16:19.779 --> 01:16:21.140
as they become important.

01:16:21.140 --> 01:16:22.740
So it truly is like,

01:16:22.740 --> 01:16:24.500
and, you know, those of us who have worked on it,

01:16:24.500 --> 01:16:25.939
in some ways it's kind of a headache

01:16:25.939 --> 01:16:28.259
because there's a lot of layers,

01:16:28.259 --> 01:16:30.740
a lot of like, oh, this part can't know about R,

01:16:30.740 --> 01:16:32.580
but this is the part that knows about R,

01:16:32.580 --> 01:16:33.700
but it is on purpose

01:16:33.700 --> 01:16:35.859
so that we can build a tool

01:16:35.859 --> 01:16:38.259
that will support you for quite a long time,

01:16:38.259 --> 01:16:41.060
be an excellent tool for your data analysis,

01:16:41.060 --> 01:16:42.100
depending on, you know,

01:16:42.100 --> 01:16:43.700
what happens 10 years from now,

01:16:43.700 --> 01:16:44.500
20 years from now,

01:16:45.220 --> 01:16:47.779
as you move on in your career.

01:16:47.779 --> 01:16:51.060
So it is, you know, it is not PyStudio

01:16:51.060 --> 01:16:53.220
the way like an RStudio for a Python would be.

01:16:53.220 --> 01:16:54.500
It is something that is built

01:16:54.500 --> 01:16:56.500
to be truly, truly polyglot.

01:16:57.220 --> 01:16:59.379
I'll give an equal kind of trolling answer,

01:16:59.379 --> 01:17:01.540
which is one of my good friends at Posit,

01:17:01.540 --> 01:17:04.100
by the way, Posit, Positron,

01:17:04.100 --> 01:17:05.060
there's some connection there,

01:17:05.700 --> 01:17:07.620
but my good friend, Ron Bloom,

01:17:07.620 --> 01:17:09.939
Posit Ron, and he's a QA engineer

01:17:09.939 --> 01:17:11.060
that does some testing.

01:17:11.060 --> 01:17:12.419
So that's the real secret

01:17:12.419 --> 01:17:13.379
is it's named after him.

01:17:15.939 --> 01:17:16.439
Okay.

01:17:17.620 --> 01:17:19.379
Let me say one final thing.

01:17:19.379 --> 01:17:21.459
So us as a team and anybody else

01:17:21.459 --> 01:17:23.700
who's here at PositConf

01:17:24.580 --> 01:17:26.819
who is working on Positron

01:17:26.819 --> 01:17:29.459
is going to be in the lounge tomorrow morning.

01:17:29.459 --> 01:17:30.899
We're going to have an open Q&A,

01:17:30.899 --> 01:17:31.939
a more casual Q&A.

01:17:31.939 --> 01:17:32.819
So if you want to come up

01:17:32.819 --> 01:17:33.939
and ask us questions,

01:17:33.939 --> 01:17:36.419
we invite you before the keynote tomorrow

01:17:36.419 --> 01:17:38.740
to join us in the lounge.

01:17:38.740 --> 01:17:39.779
And that's it for us, right?

01:17:39.779 --> 01:17:42.500
Yep. Thank you so much.

01:17:53.700 --> 01:17:54.200
Thank you.

